    <finding>
    {"title": "Priority Manipulation and Selective Execution via Ignored Errors", "description": "Root cause & mechanism\nThe permissionless crank instruction transfer_category_vestings is intended to process (transfer and advance) vesting state sequentially across multiple investor and functional categories in a single \u201ccycle\u201d. Instead of propagating failures, it deliberately converts each per-category Result into a boolean via .is_err(), emits a msg! log (e.g., \u201cFailed to transfer tokens from master to pre-seed!\u201d), and then continues executing subsequent categories and finally returns Ok(()).\n\nBecause each category\u2019s token destination account is supplied by the caller as an UncheckedAccount (e.g., pre_seed_ata, seed_ata, marketing_ata, etc.), a caller can intentionally make a specific per-category update fail (or simply let it fail due to runtime conditions like insufficient funds) without aborting the overall instruction. The per-category helper functions perform critical validations such as:\n- require_keys_eq!(category_ata.key(), get_associated_token_address_with_program_id(...), ErrorCode::AtaMismatch)\n- require!(category.cliff_started_at != 0, ErrorCode::TgeNotHappened)\nand perform token_2022::transfer_checked(...) when total_tokens > 0, then mutate category state such as months_claimed and (for investor categories) tokens_ready_for_claim. Any error from these checks/CPIs is swallowed by transfer_category_vestings, allowing partial completion and selective skipping.\n\nTrigger conditions / assumptions\n- The instruction transfer_category_vestings is callable by arbitrary users (acts as a crank).\n- The caller controls the category ATA accounts passed in the TransferCategoryVestings context; these are UncheckedAccount and only validated inside the helper functions.\n- At least one per-category call can be made to error while others succeed. This can be induced by:\n  1) Supplying an incorrect/dummy public key for one or more category ATAs so require_keys_eq! fails with ErrorCode::AtaMismatch (ATA mismatch against the deterministic associated token address derived via get_associated_token_address_with_program_id using token_2022::ID and either the category account address (investor categories) or category.wallet (functional categories)).\n  2) Causing/encountering a runtime transfer failure such as the master_ata being underfunded for a later transfer (e.g., limited funds due to delayed funding, partial unlocks, or a large cliff event), after earlier categories already succeeded.\n- TGE/cliff gating (category.cliff_started_at != 0) must be satisfied for a category to progress; if not, that category will error and be skipped while others may progress.\n\nImpact\n- Partial state commit across categories: some categories successfully transfer tokens and advance state (e.g., months_claimed is increased and investor categories\u2019 tokens_ready_for_claim is increased), while other categories remain stale because their update failed and was skipped; yet the overall instruction still reports success (Ok(())).\n- Breaks the intended \u201call categories together\u201d monthly transition semantics, enabling inconsistent category freshness across the system.\n- Selective execution / priority manipulation: a malicious caller can intentionally skip earlier or \u201chigher-priority\u201d categories in the sequence (e.g., pre_seed_cat) by passing invalid ATAs, so that limited funds in master_ata are instead distributed to later categories they prefer (e.g., seed_cat), bypassing the intended sequential distribution order.\n- Off-chain automation/keepers can be misled: monitoring systems may interpret the overall Ok(()) as a completed cycle even though some categories failed and were not updated.\n- Downstream claim flow disruption: investor-side logic (as referenced) may require category-level claiming to have happened for the cycle (e.g., checks like \u201cif months_elapsed != category.months_claimed as u64 { \u2026 return Ok(()) }\u201d), so skipped categories can block investor claims or otherwise desynchronize expected behavior.\n\nExploitation / reproduction notes (PoC highlights)\n1) Choose a target category to receive funds/advance (e.g., seed_cat) and identify categories executed before it (e.g., pre_seed_cat).\n2) Build a transaction calling transfer_category_vestings.\n3) For each category you want to skip (e.g., pre_seed_ata), provide a malformed account: a randomly generated/dummy pubkey or any account that is not the correct associated token address for that category and mint under Token2022. This triggers require_keys_eq!(..., ErrorCode::AtaMismatch) inside update_vesting_for_investor_category / update_vesting_for_functional_category.\n4) For the categories you want to execute normally (e.g., seed_ata and others), pass their correctly derived ATAs.\n5) Execute the transaction:\n   - The skipped category call errors (AtaMismatch) and transfer_category_vestings only logs \u201cFailed to transfer tokens from master to ...\u201d and continues.\n   - Subsequent categories execute; if master_ata has limited funds, the attacker can ensure earlier categories are skipped so available tokens are transferred to the later, preferred category.\n6) Variant: Provide all correct ATAs but rely on master_ata being underfunded for a later category transfer. Earlier categories will still complete and mutate state; later ones fail, are logged, and the instruction still returns Ok(())\u2014committing a partial cycle.\n\nCode-location anchors (if present in the inputs)\n- programs/master-token-program/src/instructions/category/claim.rs\n  - transfer_category_vestings(ctx: Context<...TransferCategoryVestings...>) -> Result<()>\n    - Per-category calls wrapped with .is_err() and only msg! on failure, then continue; ends with Ok(()).\n    - Affected categories in sequence: pre_seed_cat, seed_cat, institutional_cat, vgp_cat, founders_cat, marketing_cat, reserve_cat, liquidity_cat.\n  - TransferCategoryVestings account context:\n    - Category ATAs are UncheckedAccount and mutable: pre_seed_ata, seed_ata, institutional_ata, vgp_ata, founders_ata, marketing_ata, reserve_ata, liquidity_ata.\n  - update_vesting_for_investor_category:\n    - require_keys_eq!(category_ata.key(), get_associated_token_address_with_program_id(&category.to_account_info().key(), &mint.key(), &token_2022::ID), ErrorCode::AtaMismatch)\n    - require!(category.cliff_started_at != 0, ErrorCode::TgeNotHappened)\n    - token_2022::transfer_checked(...)\n    - State mutations: category.months_claimed = ...; category.tokens_ready_for_claim += category.total_allocated_tokens_monthly * vesting_months_claimed as u64\n  - update_vesting_for_functional_category:\n    - require_keys_eq!(category_ata.key(), get_associated_token_address_with_program_id(&category.wallet, &mint.key(), &token_2022::ID), ErrorCode::AtaMismatch)\n    - require!(category.cliff_started_at != 0, ErrorCode::TgeNotHappened)\n    - token_2022::transfer_checked(...)\n    - State mutations: category.months_claimed = ... (uses remaining-window cap via min(48u8.saturating_sub(category.months_claimed) as u64) as u8)"}
